# Copy to compose/.env (gitignored) and fill in. Phase 2 runs with the defaults
# below and NO SaaS creds (collector exports to debug). Add the Splunk/Datadog
# values + enable the exporters in otel-collector/config.yaml for Phase 1.

# --- Mesh / chaos -----------------------------------------------------------
CHAOS_TOKEN=dev-chaos-token
# Short git SHA stamped into traces as git.commit (optional; defaults to "unknown").
# Set when building:  GIT_COMMIT=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) docker compose ... build
GIT_COMMIT=unknown

# --- Postgres ---------------------------------------------------------------
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=pocpass

# --- Datadog (Phase 1) ------------------------------------------------------
DD_API_KEY=
DD_APP_KEY=
DD_SITE=datadoghq.com

# --- Splunk Cloud HEC (Phase 1) ---------------------------------------------
SPLUNK_HEC_URL=https://http-inputs-<stack>.splunkcloud.com:443/services/collector
SPLUNK_HEC_TOKEN=
SPLUNK_INDEX=main

# --- DevOps agent (Phase 4) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LLM backend: 'ollama' (default, creds-free) or 'anthropic' (requires API key)
LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
# Ollama config (only used if LLM_PROVIDER=ollama; default qwen3.5:9b tool-capable model)
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen3.5:9b
# Anthropic config (only used if LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
AGENT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# MCP endpoints (default to in-compose mock services)
SPLUNK_MCP_URL=
DATADOG_MCP_URL=
BALLERINA_TOPOLOGY_MCP_URL=
# Phase 4 §4.9 — bumped 30->40 to absorb extra discover_tools turns from
# Phase 6's federated backends. Do not go below 25 (Ollama non-determinism).
AGENT_MAX_TURNS=40
# Include toggles (Y|N) — hard on/off gate for whole backend groups on the
# proxy (federation.bal). INCLUDE_WSO2_MCP=N drops apim/mi/is from federation
# entirely (never connected/discovered/routed), even if their URLs are set.
# INCLUDE_K8S_MCP=Y adds k8s/docker (also needs --profile infra-mcp). Defaults:
# WSO2 group on, infra group off. splunk/datadog are never gated.
INCLUDE_WSO2_MCP=Y
INCLUDE_K8S_MCP=N
# WSO2-product MCP backend URLs — default to the in-compose mock servers.
# K8S_MCP_URL/DOCKER_MCP_URL default empty = disabled (see the
# --- Kubernetes / Docker MCP (Phase 6, --profile infra-mcp) --- section below).
APIM_MCP_URL=
MI_MCP_URL=
IS_MCP_URL=
K8S_MCP_URL=
DOCKER_MCP_URL=
# Optional bearer auth on the proxy's own /mcp endpoint (Refactor R4.3).
# Empty (default) = unauthenticated, matching the creds-free demo.
PROXY_API_KEY=

# WSO2 AMP observability for the agent's OWN trace (optional; separate from
# LLM_PROVIDER=amp above, which routes LLM calls — this routes OTel traces).
# Leave unset to keep shipping traces via jaeger -> otel-collector (default).
# Set AMP_TRACING_PROVIDER=amp to instead send this agent's reasoning trace
# (LLM spans w/ token counts, tool spans w/ inputs/outputs) straight to the
# AMP Console's Traces view. Requires a local AMP quick-start container
# (see README "WSO2 Agent Manager — quick-start"); generate AMP_API_KEY from
# its Setup Agent panel.
AMP_TRACING_PROVIDER=
AMP_OTEL_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:22893/otel
AMP_API_KEY=

# --- MCP server (Phase 3) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Base URL of the Splunk Cloud instance used by the Ballerina MCP server
SPLUNK_URL=https://your-splunk.splunkcloud.com

# --- WSO2-product MCP servers (Phase 6) ────────────────────────────────────
# Each defaults to MODE=mock (deterministic fixtures, creds-free). Set the
# *_MCP_MODE to 'live' + point *_BASE_URL at a real instance (e.g. the
# --profile wso2 containers below) to call the actual product.
APIM_MCP_MODE=mock
APIM_BASE_URL=https://wso2am:9443
APIM_USERNAME=admin
APIM_PASSWORD=admin
MI_MCP_MODE=mock
MI_BASE_URL=https://wso2mi:9164
MI_USERNAME=admin
MI_PASSWORD=admin
IS_MCP_MODE=mock
IS_BASE_URL=https://wso2is:9443
IS_USERNAME=admin
IS_PASSWORD=admin

# --- Kubernetes / Docker MCP (Phase 6, --profile infra-mcp) ────────────────
# Off by default (K8S_MCP_URL/DOCKER_MCP_URL above are empty = disabled).
# `make infra-up` prepares a container-reachable kubeconfig and starts both.
# Per-label registration-filter overrides (comma-separated glob patterns) —
# see federation.bal isToolAllowed (Refactor R4.2). Defaults already deny k8s
# writes and allow only read-style docker tools; only set these to widen or
# narrow that further.
K8S_MCP_DENY=
K8S_MCP_ALLOW=
DOCKER_MCP_ALLOW=
DOCKER_MCP_DENY=

# --- Runbook write paths (Phase 7.1/7.2) ────────────────────────────────────
# restart-service/scale-service only ever mutate real infrastructure through
# callBackendToolDirect (never a plain agent tool call — see runbooks.bal).
# Both default OFF; leave false unless you have a real, disposable k8s
# cluster wired in via --profile infra-mcp and want to test the real path.
K8S_WRITE_ENABLED=false
RESTART_CONTAINER_PREFIX=devops-poc-

# --- Real WSO2 products (--profile wso2, optional) ─────────────────────────
# Heavier local containers for a genuine live-mode run (real APIM/MI/IS behind
# the apim-mcp/mi-mcp/is-mcp servers). Budget ~5GB RAM and a 1-3 min cold start.
#
# Images are built LOCALLY from extracted product distributions:
#   make wso2-build-images        # uses WSO2_SRC_DIR (default ~/dev/wso2)
# The build layers each pure-Java product onto a multi-arch Temurin 11 base, so
# the images run NATIVELY on arm64 or amd64 — no QEMU emulation, no registry
# pull. Point WSO2_SRC_DIR at the parent of your apim/ is/ mi/ extracted folders
# (or override AM_DIR / IS_DIR / MI_DIR). MI uses 4.3.0 (4.2.0's extracted dir
# had a broken OSGi state); APIM 4.2.0 and IS 6.1.0.
#
# Bring the real products up in live mode with a single command:
#   make wso2-up      # sets *_MCP_MODE=live + INCLUDE_WSO2_MCP=Y, starts --profile wso2
# or set the three *_MCP_MODE=live vars above yourself and run --profile wso2.
# `make wso2-down` stops the products and reverts the MCP servers to mock.
WSO2_SRC_DIR=
